annotationA: Accessory gland protein 76A is a protein that shows homology to the serpin serine endopeptidase inhibitor family but is predicted to be non-inhibitory. It is produced in the male accessory glands and transferred to females during mating
annotationB: Accessory gland protein 53C14c, isoform A; It is involved in the biological process described with: multicellular organism reproduction
